text: The Muskogee Oilers were a professional, minor league baseball team that played in the Western League in 1933. They began the year in Wichita, Kansas as the Wichita Oilers, but moved to Muskogee, Oklahoma after being evicted from their park in Wichita.The Western League by W.C. Madden and Patrick Stewart Hall of Famer Rube Marquard managed the team at one point, while All- Star pitchers Mort Cooper and Kirby Higbe played for the club.Team roster ==References== Category:Baseball teams established in 1933 Category:Baseball teams disestablished in 1933 Category:Defunct minor league baseball teams Category:Defunct baseball teams in Kansas Category:1933 establishments in Kansas Category:1933 disestablishments in Kansas Category:Defunct baseball teams in Oklahoma
